title: About Me
text:
I provide data-driven strategies to some of the world’s most beloved brands through quantitative and qualitative research and consulting. Organized and efficient project/program manager with a love of cross-functional collaboration. Passionate about learning and upskilling others. I’m comfortable with ambiguity and thrive in fast paced, entrepreneurial environments.
Advanced PowerPoint and Excel skills. Data analysis + visualization experience in R, SPSS, and Tableau. Learning SQL.
Fluent in Spanish (speaking, writing, reading), learning Portuguese.
Graduate level coursework in data analytics (R, SQL, Excel), data science (R), statistics, economics, marketing management.
Prior international work experience in program management, volunteer coordination, and program measurement and evaluation.



Master of Science - Data Analytics and Computational Social Sciences University of Massachusetts Amherst Spring 2026 (Expected)
BA, Political Science, International Studies, Latin American Studies, History Elon University 2007 - 2011
Thanks for checking out my web site!
